<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Ramelron</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-24 03:38:20</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Okay, to clarify, Pyzjn is her name, approx lvl 15 necro with pet. I have camped her with a lvl 30 shaman and recently been camping her with my lvl 20 druid (don't underestimate the power of Tracking skill). In a total of 3 nights of camping her, I have slain her 4 times, one time I was on her so fast with my druid tracking her, she hadn't even had time to summon her pet. Needless to say, I don't know what I was doing right, except that like the other posts advise, I was killing everything undead or not that came anywhere near the ruins...this included rats, bats, wolves, bears, snakes and of course the putrids and dreads. Four spawns in three nights, and of course not a single stone, but I do have 4 nice rusty daggers to show for my time...my advice is to kill anything that either spawns in the ruins or walks to the ruins ESPECIALLY if it just walks up and sits in the middle motionless.</font></td></tr></table>
