<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Synlien Wulvenspirit</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-02 04:17:20</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Yesterday night feeling bored of the whole camping philosophy I decided to a bit of travelling from Lake Rather to who knows where.<BR>
<BR>
I made my way up thru South Karana, headed into North Karana.  I killed a few wisps I found on track and a beetle or two as I passed through.  Heading into West Karan I came across the Bandit camp closest to the North Karana border.  I proceded to masacre all inhabitants of this fould camp.  Got myself one of those nice bandit sashes they carry and a grim satisfaction for ridding the Karanas of a few more bandits.  I decided to head west for no reason other than to visit my old hunting grounds, stopping on the way to kill a few more straggling bandits till I finally found myself in Qeynos Hills.  <BR>
<BR>
I thought I could rid the hills of a few rabid beasts to help the locals.  Sat around a second looking at the tracks in the mud to no avail.  No rabid beasts to be seen, so I set out towards Surefall Glade maybe I would happen across a rabid on the way.  I pass Blackburrow and low and behold a ranger ahead of me seems to be in distress.  Seems he has been felled upon by a group of dread corpses 4 to be exact and a evil little necromancer names Pyzjin.  By the time I got there it was to late for the Ranger so I decided I would get revenge for this person and kill what seemed to be the ring leader Pyzjin.  I hit her with careless lightningtaking her to about 25% of her life.  I charge in because I was out of mana due to the bandit hunting earlier.  *OOC*  Now I figured I would kill her not knowing what she dropped.  I had seen many a high lvl camping around this location never understood why or took the initiative to find out.  So I risked killing this necro who conned green at lvl 20.  I got put down to 2 bubs of life when she died looted the GBS and a rusty dagger and ran for BB.  Made it to BB asked a guild mate what it was and how much it was worth.  He couldn't believe it and I couldn't believe the price I got for it. 15kpp so moral of the story is sometimes it helps to play the game it should be by not camping.  You never know what can happen. :)<BR>
<BR>
Synlien Wulvenspirit<BR>
20th season Druid<BR>
Knights of Lore<BR>
The Nameless Server</font></td></tr></table>
